Subject: Re: [T2] sealant for pushrod tube seals

On Fri, 8 Feb 2008, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> Jon Stiles wrote:
> > For a type 4 motor. If you clean the galleys and pushrod tubes and make sure
> > the pushrod tubes are not bent or dented at the ends, all you need is a
> > little motor oil to slip them into place.

> This is what I did when I first rebuilt the engine, and now 60,000 miles
> later it's leaking all over.

I've not used it for this purpose, but it seems like this is an excellent
place for Hylomar.  It is like thick grease that isn't slippary and
doesn't harden.  It's available at Harley Davidson dealers.


